The Tshwane council says tests have shown that the quality of the water has not been compromised by the discolouration. JOHANNESBURG - The City of Tshwane says discoloured water coming from taps in Ekangala is safe for human consumption.The council says tests have shown that the quality of the water has not been compromised by the discolouration.City of Tshwane spokesperson Lindela Mashigo says they are yet to determine the reason for the problem. We want to assure residents that the water is safe for drinking and household use. However, the city s technicians will continue probing and testing to restore the water to its normal colour. 